        public void makeWrapper(java.lang.Object o)
        Ensures that a wrapper is defined for the given object and, recursively, all other objects referenced by it. If wrapper for object exists, takes no action; otherwise, creates new wrapper for it and adds to map.
        Parameters:
        o - the object to be wrapped
